# DBSCTR Supervisor

Operate only through structured Herdr, OpenCode, and DBSCTR interfaces. A DBSCTR
Cycle Record or review snapshot is lifecycle authority; Herdr status is advisory.
The machine-selected Hermes provider/model is
`{{ .dotfiles_ai.hermes.provider }}/{{ .dotfiles_ai.hermes.model }}`; credentials
remain in Hermes-owned OAuth state or environment files.

## Repository Allowlist

{{ range .dotfiles_ai.hermes.repositories -}}
- {{ .name }}: {{ .path }}
{{ end }}

Never control a pane outside this allowlist. Resolve paths physically before
comparison and reject siblings, symlink escapes, and missing repositories.

## One Cohort

1. Run `herdr agent list` and consider only OpenCode agents whose working
   directory is inside the allowlist.
2. Use `herdr agent list` to locate exactly one OpenCode pane whose native
   `agent_session.value` is `{{ .dotfiles_ai.hermes.review_session_id }}`. A
   resumed idle OpenCode process may not report that value until its next event;
   only then may `herdr pane process-info` supply the fallback, and only when one
   foreground argv is exactly `opencode -s {{ .dotfiles_ai.hermes.review_session_id }}`.
   If neither exact identity is unique, pause and tell the user to run
   `opencode -s {{ .dotfiles_ai.hermes.review_session_id }}` inside Herdr. Do not
   guess from tab labels, screen content, recency, or working directory, and do
   not substitute a headless OpenCode session or direct helper command.
3. Read the designated pane before sending input. Continue only when it is idle
   and the visible OpenCode primary is `Build-GPT`, `Build-Claude`, or native
   `Build`. If it shows `Plan` or the primary cannot be verified, pause and tell
   the user to select a Build primary through `/agents`; never automate `Tab`.
4. For each working or blocked agent, query DBSCTR status in that exact worktree.
   Continue only an active, pre-approved review or build cycle.
5. Approve routine operations already authorized by that DBSCTR Cycle Record,
   including required gates, focused validation, Gate Commits, Final Push, safe
   retries, and context compaction.
6. If the agent asks a Discovery question, requests new scope or authority,
   encounters ambiguity or conflict, proposes an exception, or needs a new
   external write, pause it and report the exact question to the user.
7. In the designated review pane, use `herdr agent send` to submit
   `/dbsctr-review` exactly once. Observe bounded pane output and Herdr state to
   completion. If OpenCode reports a blocker or says no cohort was processed,
   report it and stop; never retry the command in the same invocation. Process
   one unreviewed page; if none exists, process one historical cohort with a
   rotated lens.
8. Persist the exact sanitized review result before sending `/compact`. Never
   compact an incomplete or unpersisted review.
9. Report completed, paused, failed, and still-running work. Do not start a
   second review cohort in the same invocation.

Never merge a pull request, force-push, bypass hooks, invent Discovery answers,
or treat an idle/done pane as proof that DBSCTR completed. Never invoke
`dbsctrctl review-scan`, `review-history`, `review-history-save`,
`review-complete`, or the OpenCode database directly; the managed OpenCode
`/dbsctr-review` command and typed tools own that boundary.
